Cut!

1202
01:20:57,080 --> 01:20:58,680
She still didn't say it!

1203
01:21:04,040 --> 01:21:05,040
Excuse me, sir,

1204
01:21:05,240 --> 01:21:06,040
do you know

1205
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:07,760
some women here

1206
01:21:07,920 --> 01:21:11,440
no longer call
their husbands "Mr."?

1207
01:21:12,040 --> 01:21:16,000
Miss Tahereh
cannot manage to say it either.

1208
01:21:16,440 --> 01:21:20,400
I don't think it will seem
implausible in the film.

1209
01:21:22,440 --> 01:21:24,200
No, it won't seem implausbile.

1210
01:21:24,360 --> 01:21:25,360
- One more time?
- No.

1211
01:21:25,520 --> 01:21:26,720
- Is that a wrap?
- Yes.

1212
01:21:26,959 --> 01:21:30,059
Thanks, guys.
Let's clear everything away.

1213
01:21:30,160 --> 01:21:32,040
Thank you, Mr. Jafarian.

1214
01:21:33,080 --> 01:21:36,080
Hossein, put the glasses in the car.
It's getting late.

1215
01:21:37,040 --> 01:21:39,160
Tahereh, pick up your book.
It's over.

1216
01:21:39,320 --> 01:21:40,840
- For me?
- Yes.

1217
01:21:41,440 --> 01:21:43,600
You won't say
your lines properly.

1218
01:21:44,240 --> 01:21:46,320
Where are the Ahmadpour boys?

1219
01:21:48,080 --> 01:21:51,720
Put your flower pots in the car.

1220
01:21:51,880 --> 01:21:54,480
Tahereh, take your flower-pot too.

1221
01:21:57,800 --> 01:22:00,640
Do you know which one it is?
Don't take somebody else's.

1222
01:22:01,640 --> 01:22:04,120
Hurry...
Pick up your flower-pots.

1223
01:22:04,960 --> 01:22:07,640
Wait, let Tahereh come down first.

1224
01:22:09,280 --> 01:22:10,840
Put them in the back.

1225
01:22:11,600 --> 01:22:12,720
We're leaving now.

1226
01:22:13,520 --> 01:22:15,320
Run, children, hurry.

1227
01:22:18,920 --> 01:22:20,720
Can't you find your flower-pots?

1228
01:22:21,920 --> 01:22:23,560
How many did you have, Babak?

1229
01:22:24,240 --> 01:22:26,840
- I had two.
- Don't dawdle, come on.

1230
01:22:27,080 --> 01:22:29,040
It had two red flowers.
It's not here!

1231
01:22:29,240 --> 01:22:30,840
Look for it then, but hurry.

1232
01:22:31,920 --> 01:22:33,600
Isn't it the one on the corner?

1233
01:22:33,760 --> 01:22:36,360
There. Take it,
there on the corner.

1234
01:22:36,960 --> 01:22:38,920
Careful you don't break the stem.

1235
01:22:43,480 --> 01:22:46,400
Put it in the back somewhere.

1236
01:22:50,160 --> 01:22:51,760
Where's Mr. Nazari?

1237
01:22:56,880 --> 01:22:59,960
- Is the minibus here yet?
- It's on its way.

1238
01:23:00,840 --> 01:23:03,840
Tahereh, put it in the back
and then sit down, I'm coming.

1239
01:23:19,520 --> 01:23:23,320
Hossein, change your shoes
and put the flower-pots away.

1240
01:23:23,480 --> 01:23:24,520
All right.

1241
01:23:25,520 --> 01:23:27,560
Let's take down the canvas.

1242
01:23:33,560 --> 01:23:35,080
Hossein, do me a favour,

1243
01:23:35,240 --> 01:23:38,400
untie the ropes.
We're putting the canvas away.

1244
01:23:38,800 --> 01:23:40,000
All right, sir.

1245
01:23:40,160 --> 01:23:42,480
Can you serve us some tea?

1246
01:23:43,600 --> 01:23:45,120
I just did!

1247
01:23:45,640 --> 01:23:48,000
Yes, but Reza drank my cup.

1248
01:23:50,160 --> 01:23:53,200
Guys, Hossein's tired,
leave him alone.

1249
01:23:53,920 --> 01:23:57,920
Put the glasses in the car
and get in.

1250
01:23:58,840 --> 01:24:01,920
Mr. Karimi,
don't put that in the car.

1251
01:24:02,080 --> 01:24:03,800
Wait for the minibus.

1252
01:24:05,720 --> 01:24:08,360
But there won't be room
in the minibus.

1253
01:24:08,520 --> 01:24:09,800
What do we do, Mr. Panahi?

1254
01:24:09,960 --> 01:24:12,880
Let the children go first,
the minibus will soon be here.

1255
01:24:13,040 --> 01:24:16,160
Let the children go first,
the minibus will soon be here.

1256
01:24:16,320 --> 01:24:18,800
We have to be organized
and professional.

1257
01:24:18,960 --> 01:24:21,120
Three people can take the minibus,

1258
01:24:21,320 --> 01:24:24,600
with the flower-pots on their knees
and still be comfortable.

1259
01:24:24,760 --> 01:24:28,080
Your things weren't that heavy!

1260
01:24:28,840 --> 01:24:30,720
Why didn't you sort something out
with Jafarian?

1261
01:24:33,040 --> 01:24:35,480
Let's be professional!

1262
01:24:39,840 --> 01:24:41,400
Why all this gear?

1263
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:45,000
In case it rains.

1264
01:24:45,600 --> 01:24:48,160
We have to consider
every possibility.

1265
01:25:02,040 --> 01:25:05,440
The children have got exams,
take them back quickly.

1266
01:25:25,200 --> 01:25:26,400
Mrs. Shiva?

1267
01:25:30,800 --> 01:25:32,080
Mr. Panahi...

1268
01:25:34,920 --> 01:25:36,840
The girl has gone!

1269
01:25:37,040 --> 01:25:38,920
- Who has gone?
- Tahereh.

1270
01:25:45,040 --> 01:25:47,840
Tahereh, wait, we'll drive you back.
It's a long way.

1271
01:25:48,000 --> 01:25:49,360
I know a short-cut.

1272
01:25:49,560 --> 01:25:52,040
The minibus will be here
in 5 minutes.

1273
01:26:03,720 --> 01:26:06,680
Hossein, can't you see
we're arguing over transport?

1274
01:26:06,840 --> 01:26:09,560
You're young, you can walk.
Go on!

1275
01:26:54,640 --> 01:26:55,680
Tahereh!

1276
01:27:11,560 --> 01:27:14,240
Miss Tahereh...
I might not see you again.

1277
01:27:14,440 --> 01:27:16,120
If you want to give me a reply,

1278
01:27:16,320 --> 01:27:17,680
give it to me now.

1279
01:27:17,920 --> 01:27:22,240
No, don't listen
to your grandmother.

1280
01:27:22,640 --> 01:27:24,240
Old women only ever think

1281
01:27:25,320 --> 01:27:29,440
of rich men,
who own houses and factories.

1282
01:27:30,000 --> 01:27:33,600
They only think of them.

1283
01:27:34,600 --> 01:27:38,800
But intelligence and understanding
are important too.

1284
01:27:39,280 --> 01:27:42,720
You haven't got a father or mother.
You need a good husband.

1285
01:27:43,400 --> 01:27:45,960
Not just any old crook
or any old fool.

1286
01:27:46,160 --> 01:27:49,480
I really want to live with you.
I'm not trying to trick you.

1287
01:27:49,640 --> 01:27:52,560
God is my witness,
it's not your beauty.

1288
01:27:53,000 --> 01:27:56,080
nor anything else,
I just want you to have...

1289
01:27:56,280 --> 01:27:59,520
a place in life,
so that you don't have to worry.

1290
01:28:00,480 --> 01:28:02,680
Come on, let's live together,
hand in hand.

1291
01:28:02,840 --> 01:28:04,680
Answer me

1292
01:28:06,240 --> 01:28:08,280
You've got a tongue!
The good Lord gave you

1293
01:28:08,480 --> 01:28:10,720
a tongue to give an answer
to someone like me.

1294
01:28:16,640 --> 01:28:18,560
If you don't want to answer,

1295
01:28:18,720 --> 01:28:21,800
then I want an explanation
about that look you gave me

1296
01:28:21,960 --> 01:28:23,520
at the cemetery.

1297
01:28:23,680 --> 01:28:26,640
That look that drew me to you
and made me follow you

1298
01:28:26,800 --> 01:28:29,200
all this time
to get an answer from you.

1299
01:28:29,360 --> 01:28:32,440
I want your reply,
not your grandmother's.

1300
01:28:32,640 --> 01:28:35,560
I don't want to speak to her again,
I don't want to see her.

1301
01:28:35,840 --> 01:28:38,640
When she got married,

1302
01:28:39,040 --> 01:28:41,240
or when your parents
- God bless them -

1303
01:28:41,440 --> 01:28:44,720
got married,
did they have a house? No!

1304
01:28:45,160 --> 01:28:48,720
We're going to work too,
we're going to build our house too.

1305
01:28:48,880 --> 01:28:52,560
Your grandmother says
without a house, I won't find a wife.

1306
01:28:52,840 --> 01:28:56,480
I'll work and, little by little,
I'll have a house too.

1307
01:28:56,640 --> 01:28:58,360
I'm just as capable as anyone else.

1308
01:28:58,840 --> 01:29:01,400
I'm no worse than anyone else
and I say

1309
01:29:01,600 --> 01:29:04,400
we can live together,
and people will envy us!

1310
01:29:04,640 --> 01:29:06,360
We're just as good as anyone else!

1311
01:29:06,560 --> 01:29:09,040
Who had a house around here?
Ask anyone!

1312
01:29:09,240 --> 01:29:12,760
Did they have a house
when they got married?

1313
01:29:13,240 --> 01:29:15,120
Even rich people,

1314
01:29:15,280 --> 01:29:18,480
when they get married,
don't have a house.

1315
01:29:18,720 --> 01:29:21,040
They move in with their parents

1316
01:29:21,280 --> 01:29:23,360
for a while and find a house.

1317
01:29:23,520 --> 01:29:25,720
You have to work hard.
You have to be brave.

1318
01:29:26,160 --> 01:29:28,440
The director said it.

1319
01:29:28,840 --> 01:29:30,480
The people who died,

1320
01:29:31,280 --> 01:29:33,080
did they know?

1321
01:29:33,280 --> 01:29:35,040
He must know

1322
01:29:35,480 --> 01:29:38,080
He studied in the city.

1323
01:29:38,280 --> 01:29:41,000
In Teheran.
That's a big city.

1324
01:29:41,320 --> 01:29:43,880
He studied.
He knows what he's talking about.

1325
01:29:44,120 --> 01:29:47,120
Listen to him.
It's logical.

1326
01:29:47,280 --> 01:29:48,720
You have to admit it.

1327
01:29:48,920 --> 01:29:50,640
And even if you don't agree,

1328
01:29:50,840 --> 01:29:53,080
say something!
React!

1329
01:29:53,320 --> 01:29:56,000
Give me an answer today

1330
01:29:56,160 --> 01:29:58,680
The shoot is over
and I won't see you again.

1331
01:29:58,840 --> 01:30:01,480
If you don't answer today,

1332
01:30:01,680 --> 01:30:03,560
I won't bother you anymore.

1333
01:30:03,800 --> 01:30:05,200
Give me your answer.

1334
01:30:05,400 --> 01:30:07,880
If you love me, say:
"Yes, I love you"!

1335
01:30:08,080 --> 01:30:11,680
If you don't,
explain that look,

1336
01:30:11,840 --> 01:30:14,120
that look you gave me
in the cemetery.

1337
01:30:14,320 --> 01:30:16,840
Since that look,
I've been following you.

1338
01:30:17,480 --> 01:30:20,080
I've been saying to myself
that you want me,

1339
01:30:20,240 --> 01:30:22,640
but that you're scared
of your grandmother!

1340
01:30:23,360 --> 01:30:25,800
Some girls
are more beautiful than you!

1341
01:30:26,520 --> 01:30:28,320
Better than you!

1342
01:30:28,720 --> 01:30:30,640
I could marry one, but I won't!

1343
01:30:30,800 --> 01:30:32,840
I want to marry you,

1344
01:30:33,360 --> 01:30:35,320
you who have
neither father nor mother.

1345
01:30:35,480 --> 01:30:37,920
What are you thinking?
You're not speaking.

1346
01:30:40,360 --> 01:30:44,320
At least give me
the flower-pot to carry.

1347
01:30:44,840 --> 01:30:46,960
If I'd known it was yours,

1348
01:30:47,120 --> 01:30:49,400
I'd have watered it.
I wouldn't have let

1349
01:30:49,560 --> 01:30:51,600
Mohammad touch it.

1350
01:30:54,000 --> 01:30:57,200
Have you got
a heart of stone or what?

1351
01:30:58,600 --> 01:31:00,240
Your heart's made of stone!

1352
01:31:25,920 --> 01:31:29,800
Do you only think
of the way you look?

1353
01:31:30,400 --> 01:31:31,800
I'm just doing it for you,

1354
01:31:31,960 --> 01:31:33,920
to give you a future.

1355
01:31:34,080 --> 01:31:36,000
Hossein can have plenty of women...

1356
01:31:36,160 --> 01:31:37,760
I can find one anywhere.

1357
01:31:45,720 --> 01:31:48,720
Tahereh, please, answer me.

1358
01:31:48,920 --> 01:31:50,400
If someone saw us together,

1359
01:31:50,560 --> 01:31:53,480
he'd think we were betrothed.

1360
01:31:53,840 --> 01:31:55,160
He'd never guess

1361
01:31:55,161 --> 01:31:58,161
that you won't reply
or that you haven't got a tongue!

